    "actions_taken": [
      "Platform shut-in ordered by BSEE",
      "Failed valves removed and replaced",
      "Fuel gas scrubber replaced with automatic fluid dumps",
      "Pneumatic pumps replaced with electric pumps",
      "Vessels cleaned of sand and debris",
      "Safety devices tested"
    ],
    "summary": "Multiple pollution events occurred at WD Block 73 A Platform from March 20-22, 2019. First event: 14 barrels of oil discharged through produced water system due to gas compressor shutdown causing fluid surge and loss of interphase levels in separation vessels. Second event: Failed pneumatic oil pumps sprayed oil to Gulf. Third event: Sump tank overflow during cleanup. Six safety devices were found bypassed during abnormal conditions.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Review Cox's LOTO procedures and documentation",
      "Review JSA procedures for equipment replacement tasks"
    ],
